        <body>       
                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>Orange&#44; N. J. April 10th 1891<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev. Dr. Morais<lb/>
                Philadelphia<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev Sir<lb/></p>
            <p>I am led to believe<lb/> that you are at the Head of a Hebrew<lb/> college in your city&#44; if such is the<lb/> fact&#44; you can do us a favor.  Our congre<lb/>gation wants a young man&#44; who would<lb/> take a situation&#44; as a Preacher&#44; Teacher<lb/> in <sic>hebrew</sic> &#38; Chazan&#44; we would pay about<lb/> 500&#45;600 Doll. pr Anum&#44; as we only have 25<lb/> Members&#44; about 12&#45;16 children to teach<lb/> all attending Public <sic>scool</sic>&#44; the preaching<lb/> of course would not be very often&#44; for<lb/> while we have Minyan Friday evenings<lb/> &#38; <sic>Sathurday</sic> mornings&#44; the attendance<lb/> is not such that a sermon would<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>be wanted.  Still we want a young<lb/> man of American Ideas&#44; of push and<lb/> <sic>energie</sic>&#44; but not a radical reformer<lb/> who should teach the children how<lb/> to imitate <hi rend="underline">the Goj</hi>.  I hope Dear<lb/> &#38; Reverend Sir&#44; that you will excuse<lb/> the imposition&#44; of taking up your<lb/> valuable time&#44; anticipating<lb/> your esteemed answer<lb/> I beg leave to remain<lb/> my dear Sir Respectfully yours<lb/> S. J. Klauber<lb/> Presidt.<lb/> of Congregation Sharey Tefiloh.<lb/></p>
            </body>
    </text>
